The paper deals with the design of interactive clustering algorithms, which is a problem in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses stability assumptions and local changes, which are concepts related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The use of algorithms to produce accurate clusterings also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. The paper also mentions real-world data, indicating a potential connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DB (Databases).
